originalText.text:
HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.
I visited this guesthouse for the first time 8 years ago and I keep going back because I have so many great memories. It just keeps getting better all the time. It is in a perfect location to use as a jumping board to go anywhere you want in New York. High Line is a short walk away. The room was very quiet, old-style and comfortable. One of the best gay guesthouses I have stayed at. I love it, and the owners are friendly and wonderful.

I had a wonderful 7 nights stay.
The staff are friendly and the owner of the hotel is extremely kind and will go to extremes to help your stay comfortable.Nothing seemed to be a bother.
I was made to feel more than welcome on my arrival and the warm approach continued throughout my time there.
I hope to return again one day.
Thank you Charles for making my week in NYC that extra special.
Ric in London
